SIMPLE: snowcap
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snowcap
<hw>Snow"cap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
very small humming bird (<spn>Microchaera albocoronata</spn>) native of
New Grenada.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The feathers of the top of the head are white and
snining, the body blue black with a purple and bronzy luster. The name
is applied also to <spn>Microchaera parvirostris</spn> of Central
America, which is similar in color.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snow-capped</ent>⟦br⟧
